  "prompt": "Why is M&M's motto \"melts in your mouth, not in your hand\"?",
  "response": "M&M's motto, \"melts in your mouth, not in your hand,\" emphasizes the candy's unique selling point. The slogan highlights that the chocolate inside the candy shell will melt when consumed but will not leave a mess on your hands, thanks to the hard candy coating. This characteristic makes M&M's an appealing treat, especially for kids and for snacking on-the-go, as it allows consumers to enjoy chocolate without the worry of getting sticky fingers. The slogan has become a memorable and effective part of M&M's branding, reinforcing the product's convenience and cleanliness.",
